# How it works internally — very high level

Think of it like this:

```text
.NET runtime
   |
   | emits runtime measurements
   | GC, memory, CPU, JIT, ThreadPool, exceptions, timers, locks
   v
System.Runtime Meter / runtime APIs
   |
   | OpenTelemetry runtime instrumentation subscribes/listens
   v
OpenTelemetry MeterProvider
   |
   | aggregates + attaches resource attributes
   | service.name, service.version, deployment.environment, etc.
   v
Exporter
   |
   | OTLP / Prometheus / vendor exporter
   v
Observability backend
```

In application code, your internal library likely wraps something equivalent to:

```csharp
services.AddOpenTelemetry()
    .WithMetrics(metrics =>
    {
        metrics.AddRuntimeInstrumentation();
        metrics.AddOtlpExporter();
    });
```

So when your library option is enabled, it adds runtime instrumentation to the app’s **metrics pipeline**.

