dotnet.gc.collections	May increase as allocation pressure grows
dotnet.gc.last_collection.heap.size	May increase if retained objects remain
dotnet.thread_pool.queue.length	May increase if enough requests pile up
Request p95 latency	May increase because each request now does extra memory work and delay
Demo talk track

“This deployment introduced a bad memory allocation pattern in the consuming API. The server-side API is still responding, but the consumer now allocates and retains memory on each request. In traces, we may only see that the consumer request is slower. But with runtime metrics, we can see that memory, allocation, and GC activity increased right after the deployment. That tells us the issue is likely inside the .NET consuming service, not only in the downstream server API.”
